{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/maindepth()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns the depth of the stack of calls to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.dispatch"},{"type":"text","text":"] on any "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" in the current thread."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"mainDepth"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"symbolKind":"func","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"mainDepth()","roleHeading":"Function","externalID":"s:4GLib9mainDepthSiyF"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"mainDepth","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That is, when called from the top level, it gives "},{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". When"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"called from within a callback from [method"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.iteration","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(or [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainLoop.run"},{"type":"text","text":"], etc.) it returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1"},{"text":". When called from within","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a callback to a recursive call to [method"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.iteration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"],","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"it returns ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"2"},{"text":". And so forth.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function is useful in a situation like the following:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Imagine an extremely simple ‘garbage collected’ system."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"c","code":["static GList *free_list;","","gpointer","allocate_memory (gsize size)","{","  gpointer result = g_malloc (size);","  free_list = g_list_prepend (free_list, result);","  return result;","}","","void","free_allocated_memory (void)","{","  GList *l;","  for (l = free_list; l; l = l->next);","    g_free (l->data);","  g_list_free (free_list);","  free_list = NULL;"," }","","[...]","","while (TRUE);"," {","   g_main_context_iteration (NULL, TRUE);","   `free_allocated_memory()`;","  }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This works from an application, however, if you want to do the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"thing from a library, it gets more difficult, since you no longer","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"control the main loop. You might think you can simply use an idle","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function to make the call to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"free_allocated_memory()"},{"type":"text","text":", but that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"doesn’t work, since the idle function could be called from a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"recursive callback. This can be fixed by using [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.main_depth"},{"type":"text","text":"]"}]},{"syntax":"c","code":["gpointer","allocate_memory (gsize size)","{","  FreeListBlock *block = g_new (FreeListBlock, 1);","  block->mem = g_malloc (size);","  block->depth = g_main_depth ();","  free_list = g_list_prepend (free_list, block);","  return block->mem;","}","","void","free_allocated_memory (void)","{","  GList *l;","  ","  int depth = g_main_depth ();","  for (l = free_list; l; );","    {","      GList *next = l->next;","      FreeListBlock *block = l->data;","      if (block->depth > depth)","        {","          g_free (block->mem);","          g_free (block);","          free_list = g_list_delete_link (free_list, l);","        }","              ","      l = next;","    }","  }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is a temptation to use [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.main_depth"},{"text":"] to solve","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"problems with reentrancy. For instance, while waiting for data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to be received from the network in response to a menu item,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the menu item might be selected again. It might seem that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"one could make the menu item’s callback return immediately"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and do nothing if [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.main_depth"},{"text":"] returns a value greater than 1.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"However, this should be avoided since the user then sees selecting"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the menu item do nothing. Furthermore, you’ll find yourself adding","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"these checks all over your code, since there are doubtless many,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"many things that the user could do. Instead, you can use the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"following techniques:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gtk_widget_set_sensitive()"},{"type":"text","text":" or modal dialogs to prevent"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the user from interacting with elements while the main"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"loop is recursing."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Avoid main loop recursion in situations where you can’t handle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"arbitrary  callbacks. Instead, structure your code so that you"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"simply return to the main loop and then get called again when"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"there is more work to do."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/mainDepth()"},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","role":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","title":"MainContext","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/mainDepth()":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"mainDepth"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/mainDepth()","title":"mainDepth()","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maindepth()","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns the depth of the stack of calls to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.dispatch"},{"text":"] on any ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"text":" in the current thread.","type":"text"}]}}}